<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Suriya:
[B]Yes, this happens constantly hehehe.  But I don't mind, as long as they are reasonable about their requests.

I want them to drag the body to me and also provide a transport to near the body...ie if the corpse is in SK, i want a ride to NK and I want that corpse dragged to the bridge.

I don't take $$ (well VERY rarely) and I rarely say no, UNLESS I'm busy and committed in a group situation, then its "sorry, no can do".  If they DARE to give me a guilt trip, then they can just be on my no res list.  I have as much right to hunt and enjoy myself as they do, I'm not obligated to leave my group and my hunt at the time to save them time and xp.

For example, I was in the crypt in Sebilis the other day, and had several /tells requesting resses.  Most of them were just fine with accepting that I was busy, but one nagged and nagged, saying I should either gate out and res them (I'm bound in Trak's Teeth and they died in Paw...um ya) or die and come res them, then have the other cleric in my group res me back there.  So basically make my entire group wait while I get a teleport to NK from Trak's Teeth, run to the body, res, then they should res me back and wait on my mana?  Um no. =D


[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
